<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Sets Conditions for Air Alliance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, July 8 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission on
Wednesday set out conditions for approving two major transatlantic
airline mergers.
</P>
<P>
European Competition Commissioner Karel van Miert said that the
commission intends to approve the mergers between British Airways
and American Airlines and between Lufthansa, SAS and United
Airlines provided that certain conditions are met.
</P>
<P>
He said that the British Airways-American Airlines alliance is
obliged to cede up to 267 slots, mostly in London, while the
Lufthansa-SAS-United Airlines alliance is obliged to cede 108
slots, mostly in Frankfurt.
</P>
<P>
They also have to reduce the frequency of flights on routes on
which they are currently dominant, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
