<HEADLINE> Uganda Mourns Sudden Death of Abiola </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, July 8 (Xinhua) -- The Uganda government has received
with profound shock and sadness the news of the sudden and
untimely death of detained Nigerian politician Chief Moshood
Abiola.
</P>
<P>
A press release issued Wednesday by the President's Office
</P>
<P>
hailed Abiola as a veteran politician in Nigeria and an
eminent personality on the African continent.
</P>
<P>
He will be remembered long as a very good friend of Uganda and
an illustrious Pan-Africanist whose demise is a terrible loss not
only to the people of Nigeria but to Africa as a whole, it said.
</P>
<P>
The Ugandan government conveys sincere condolence and sympathy
to the bereaved family.
</P>
<P>
Abiola, who died of cardiac arrest Tuesday afternoon at the
age of 60, is reported to be taken ill when meeting with the
visiting U.S. officials.
</P>
<P>
Having been widely believed to have won the 1993 presidential
election in Nigeria, Abiola was locked up in 1994 by late
Nigerian President Sani Abacha who died less than a month ago.
</P>
<P>
Abacha's successor General Abdulsalam Abubakar who took power
on June 9 promised to United Nations Secretary-General Kofi Annan
that all political prisoners will be released soon.
</P>
<P>
Abiola's impending release is expected to help stabilize the
uncertain situation in the west African country and his sudden
death is regarded as the latest twist in Nigeria's rocky
political road. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
