<HEADLINE> Contact Group Demands Immediate Ceasefire in Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Members of the six-nation Contact Group
Wednesday called for an immediate ceasefire in Kosovo to pave the way
for continuous dialogue on the future status of the Serbian province.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued after a meeting in Bonn, the group,
comprising Britain, France, Germany, Italy, Russia and the United
States, said that they would seek a resolution of the UN Security
Council to press for the ceasefire.
</P>
<P>
The group also agreed to recommend "basic elements" for a
resolution concerning of future status of Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
German Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel told reporters after the
meeting that details of the recommendations would be presented in
a secret document to Belgrade and leaders of ethnic Albanians in
Kosovo. 
</P>
</TEXT>
