<HEADLINE> Djiboutian Minister Arrives in Addis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Djiboutian Minister of
Transport and Telecommunications Abdella Abdulahi Migl arrived
here Wednesday to seek support for improvement of its port.
</P>
<P>
Upon his arrival for a three-day working visit to Ethiopia#,
Abdulahi Migl told press that he will discuss with senior
Ethiopian officials about the ways of improving and strengthening
the port of Djibouti.
</P>
<P>
The minister said he will hold talks with Ethiopian officials
on various issues of common interest between the two neighboring
countries.
</P>
<P>
The Djiboutian minister was welcomed at the airport by
Kassahun Ayele, Ethiopian Minister of Trade and Industry as well
as other government officials.
</P>
<P>
After the outbreak of the Ethio-Eritrean border dispute on
May 6 this year, Ethiopia has diverted from Assab port of Eritrea
to Port Djibouti as its outlet.
</P>
<P>
According to official announcements here, about 300 freight
trucks are moving a total of 6,000 tons of goods a day through
Djibouti and 300 tons of fuel is now being transported to
Ethiopia by Ethio-Djibouti railways every day.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia has allocated three million U.S. Dollars to
improving the maritime services at the port of Djibouti. 
</P>
</TEXT>
