<HEADLINE> PNA Asks Israel to Hand Over Palestinian Remains </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, July 8 (Xinhua) -- The palestinian National
Authority (PNA) Wednesday asked Israel to hand over the remains of
hundreds of Palestinians who died in battles with Israel since the
1967 Middle East War.
</P>
<P>
The request was made in a letter sent Wednesday by Chief
Palestinian negotiator Saeb Erekat to Israeli Cabinet Secretary
Danny Naveh, according to the Jerusalem Media and Communication
Center (JMCC), a Palestinian news service based in East Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of Palestinian families are seeking an end to their
long sufferings by demanding Israel return the bodies of their
beloved ones, the letter said.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinians claimed that Israeli army had buried the
bodies of the Palestinian victims and covered the their names
since 1967.
</P>
<P>
The letter said that the PNA decided to send the letter
because it was within the framework of the Article 28 of the
Interim Agreement, under which Israel pledged to help find the
missing Palestinians or their bodies.
</P>
<P>
Copies of the letter were also sent to the International
Committee of the Red Cross, the U.S. and European Union peace
envoys for the Middle East, the JMCC added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
