<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mozambique to Begin Recruitment Registration in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, July 8 (Xinhua) -- the Mozambican government will
start recruitment registration betweem August 1 and September 30
in a bid to "fill up the army to its full strength," Defense
Minister Aguiar Mazula announced here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference, Mazula said that the
registration will cost 500 million Metical (some 420,000 U.S.
Dollars) and all the youth aged between 18 and 23 years will be
registered without exception.
</P>
<P>
According to the statistics from the Mozambican Defense
Ministry, there are about 200,000 Mozambican youths at the ages
of military service.
</P>
<P>
Mazula reiterated that Mozambique needs a small-scale force
with high mobility and capability. Though small-sized, the troops
should be educated and able to use the modern technologies and
equipment, he added.
</P>
<P>
He said that the size of the force would be decided by the
Mozambican Council of Ministers.
</P>
<P>
Currently, there are 12,000 troops in the Mozambican armed
forces. Under the peace agreement reached in 1992 by the
Mozambican government and the opposition Mozambican National
Resistance (Renamo), the government army should have a force of
30,000 troops.
</P>
<P>
He promised to provide proper payments for the new recruits
and to improve logistics and training conditions for them.
</P>
<P>
According to the Mozambique's military service law, the country's
military service system includes compulsory service of two years,
voluntary service of six years and over six years service to
train permanent carders.
</P>
<P>
The last recruitment registration was made six years ago.
</P>
</TEXT>
