<HEADLINE> OAU Chief Visits Mozambique </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Salim Ahmed Salim, Secretary
General of the Organization of African Unity (OAU), arrived here
Wednesday evening for a three-day visit in Mozambique at the
invitation of Mozambican President Joaquim Chissano.
</P>
<P>
Salim told the reporters upon his arrival at the Maputo
Airport that he hopes to meet Chissano on the changes on the
African continent as well as conflict solution.
</P>
<P>
He will also exchange views with Mozambican officials on how
to implement the resolutions adopted by the 34th OAU summit held
in Burkina Faso, on the challenges facing Africa and their
solutions.
</P>
<P>
The OAU chief felt regretful that seeking solutions to
conflicts in Africa still remain to be priority.
</P>
<P>
"Unfortunately, we still have to discuss these issues instead
of the development issues which I'd rather discuss," he said.
</P>
<P>
Salim is accompanied by his wife and Daniel Antonio, assistant
secretary general for OAU who is a Mozambican. 
</P>
