<HEADLINE> UK Defense Chief Unveils Military Shake-up Plan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 8 (Xinhua) -- British Defense Secretary George
Robertson Wednesday unveiled a large-scale military shake-up plan,
saying it will modernize the country's Armed Forces to meet the
challenges of the new century.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters at a London briefing, Robertson said the
Strategic Defense Review "is a mixture of radical change and solid
planning fused together through a process of unprecedented open
and wide consulation both within and outside the Ministry of
Defense."
</P>
<P>
"We will transform the way in which the Armed Forces do
business. New tri-service organizations will take the best from
each of the Services and miximize their collective punch,"
Robertson said.
</P>
<P>
Under the documents on the massive reforms, a Joint Rapid
Reaction Forces will be created in a bid to conduct operations
ranging from evacuation of British citizens to high intensity
conflicts.
</P>
<P>
"We will now be able to mount operations around the size of our
largest Bosnia commitment (some 15,000 personnel) at the short
notice. We will for the first time be able to conduct two of this
size operation at once," the document said.
</P>
<P>
The other major initiatives presented in Strategic Defense
Review are:
</P>
<P>
-- to purchase two new aircraft carriers, four roll-on-roll-off
container ships and four large transport aircraft
</P>
<P>
-- Trident nuclear submarines will be maintained but the number
of its warheads to be reduced from 96 to 48
</P>
<P>
-- confirm the country's commitment to purchase 232
Eurofighters
</P>
<P>
-- number of the fleet of frigates and destroyers to be cut
from 35 to 32.  
</P>
</TEXT>
