<HEADLINE> More Than 20 Die in Pakistani Road Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 9 (Xinhua) -- More than 20 people were burnt
alive and about forty others injured Thursday in a fire caused by
a head-on collision between two passenger buses in central
Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
The accident took place near Vihari, about 350 kilometers
southwest of Pakistan's Punjab provincial capital of Lahore,
according to a report of the Associated Press of Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
A passenger bus was heading towards Kasur, about 50 kilometers
south of Lahore, from Multan, about 460 kilometers southwest of
the capital, when it collided head-on with a bus coming from the
opposite direction, said the report.
</P>
<P>
The report said that immediately after the collision both
vehicles caught fire in which at least 20 passengers were burnt to
death.
</P>
<P>
The injured have been sent to hospitals for treatment, it said.
</P>
<P>
The report did not mention the cause of the accident. 
</P>
