<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, July 9 (Xinhua) -- A Palestinian delegation left
Thursday for Washington for talks with U.S. officials on the
stalled Middle East peace process, according to the Voice of
Palestine (VOP).
</P>
<P>
The delegation was led by care-taker ministers of the Local
Government Saeb Erekat and Planning and International Cooperation
Nabil Sha'ath. They will talk with U.S. Secretary of State
Madeleine Albright, VOP added.
</P>
<P>
The delegation's visit came upon a request from Albright, who
made a telephone call Wednesday night to Yasser Arafat, chairman
of the Palestinian National Authority (PNA), it said.
</P>
