percent more of the West Bank during its second stage
redeployment. The PNA has in principle accepted this formula,
which has so far been kept secret by Washington.
</P>
<P>
Israel, which still refuses to accept this proposal, repeated
on Wednesday that it could decide on this matter only after the
PNA fulfills its obligations under the signed peace accords.
</P>
<P>
Israel's demands include annulment of the anti-Israel articles
of the Palestinian Covenant by the Palestinian National Council,
handover of suspected Palestinian assailants for trial in Israel
and a halt to anti-Israeli incitement in the Palestinian
media. 
