business unit to assist small and medium-sized companies in Hong
Kong in meeting their funding and transaction service needs to
realize their business potentials.
</P>
<P>
Entitled CitiBusiness, the business unit aims at companies with
annual sales turnover below 400 million HK dollars (51.3 million
U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
CitiBusiness offers these companies a wide range of financial
solutions on competitive terms and creates extensive opportunities
for these companies backed by the bank's global network of
branches and relationships in 100 countries and territories.
</P>
<P>
Announcing the launch of CitiBusiness Thursday, T.C. Chan, head
of Global Corporate Banking for Citibank Hong Kong, said the
CitiBusiness is part of the bank's global strategy to provide
banking services to small and medium-sized enterprises.
</P>
<P>
"We see the launch of CitiBusiness especially timely in view of
the current market situation because a lot of these enterprises
need help," Chan said.
</P>
<P>
Chan said there are over 300,000 small and medium-sized
companies in Hong Kong, many of which have very good potential for
growth. He added that the Citibank aims to become long-term
partners of these companies.
</P>
<P>
Citibank is the world's leading global financial institution
and the largest U.S. bank in Hong Kong. 
