<HEADLINE> 75th Minute Most Dangerous in World Cup Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The 75th minute is the most dangerous in
a game at the World Cup finals, FIFA said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
FIFA Communicates Director Keith Cooper said statistics show that
35 goals have been scored in the 75th minute so far, higher than any
other minute of the game.
</P>
<P>
Of the 1,749 goals netted so far, 350 goals came in the last
fifteen minutes of the match, accounting for about 20 percent of all
goals. 
</P>
