<HEADLINE> China's Large Enterprise Work Commission </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The Central Committee of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) officially established its large
enterprise work commission today in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Premier Wu Bangguo, head of the work commission, spoke at
the commission's work conference today for officials from large
enterprises in Beijing. Wu said that the commission is a great way
to speed up reforms at state-owned enterprises and to establish an
administrative system for the socialist market economy.
</P>
<P>
The work commission will be responsible for watching officials
of large state-owned enterprises and state-controlled
share-holding enterprises directly under the State Council's
control, Wu explains.
</P>
<P>
Wu said the inspectors will watch the implementation of state
policies, state assets, and will audit accounts.
</P>
<P>
The purpose of inspection system is to help enterprises with
development and not to interfere in management, Wu pointed out.
</P>
