<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Malaysia to Provide Sudan Credit Facilities for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia has agreed in
principal to provide credit facilities to Sudan to buy Malaysian
palm oil under the Palm Oil Credit Payment Arrangement (POCPA),
Malaysian Primary Industries Minister Lim Keng Yaik said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The amount of credit has yet to be determined, but it could be
between 50 million to 70 million U.S. dollars either in Sudanese
currency or in Malaysian ringgit, he told reporters after meeting
Sudanese Foreign Minister Mustafa Osman Ismail at his office here.
</P>
<P>
A final agreement will be signed soon, after approval from the
cabinet, Lim said. Under the agreement, Malaysia will grant Sudan
a two-year period of deferred payment for all palm oil imported
from Malaysia, and this meant that Sudan will make the first
payment after two years of the first import (of palm oil) as
agreed under the new arrangement.
</P>
<P>
Lim hoped the credit facility would take effect within the next
two to three months.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia and Sudan have already agreed on the bilateral payment
arrangement between the two countries' central banks.
</P>
<P>
Sudan is one of the net importer of Malaysian palm oil,
importing about 40,000 to 50,000 tons of palm oil per annum.
</P>
<P>
With the new arrangement, Lim said he hoped the republic would
buy more Malaysian palm oil.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia has already provided POCPA credit facilities to six
countries -- Pakistan, Algeria, Iran, Myanmar, Iraq and Cuba --
with credit facilities worth almost 300 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Apart from the cash term payment, Lim said he also raised
another method of credit payment which is via counter-trade with
Sudan.
</P>
<P>
Sudan, as a producer of groundnut oil and sesame seeds oil,
could make payment to Malaysia with the commodities and Malaysia
in turn could export the commodities to third countries, Lim said.
</P>
<P>
The Sudanese foreign minister arrived here Monday for a
five-day visit to Malaysia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
