<HEADLINE> E.U. Funds for Technical Innovations in SMEs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The European Union has pledged 3.5
million ECUs (3.86 million U.S. dollars) in funding to facilitate
technical innovations in European small and medium-sized
enterprises (SMEs).
</P>
<P>
The money will be channelled into the enterprises in the form of
the I-TEC2 extension program, the European Commission, executive
arm of the 15-member bloc, announced Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The body has promised 250 million ECUs (275 million dollars)
since last July for early stage investment in the SMEs via a
program, known as I-TEC, or Innovation and Technology Equity
Capital.
</P>
<P>
Edith Cresson, European Commissioner responsible for research
and innovation, said the funding is expected to encourage venture
capital investment into technologically-innovative enterprises
which lack private capital.
</P>
<P>
The I-TEC2 extension, like I-TEC, is run by the European
Commission in collaboration with the European Investment Fund and
is expected to entice more venture capital operators into the
programs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
