<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Finds New Proof of Japanese Invasion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, July 9 (Xinhua) -- A complete map of the "Greater East
Asia Co-prosperity Sphere" has been discovered recently in east
China's Jiangsu Province, offering new proof of the Japanese
invasion of China during World War II.
</P>
<P>
An old gentleman named Pan, living in Huaiyin city in Jiangsu,
made the map public. It was one of the 32 maps that were seized from
the Japanese command by his father during a battle in Changchun
city in northeast China in 1945.
</P>
<P>
The map, 50 cm long and 30 cm wide, includes China, Mongolia,
Nepal, Thailand, Vietnam, Laos, the Phillippines, Malaysia and
Indonesia in the so-called "co-prosperity sphere."
</P>
<P>
Pan consulted several museums around the country, but found no
map similar to this one. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980709.0115 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-09 12:37 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran, Pakistan Call for Joint Efforts to Solve </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Iran and Pakistan have called for
joint efforts to help solve the Afghan crisis, the Iranian
official news agency IRNA reported on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
In his meeting with Pakistani envoy for Afghan affairs Iftikhar
Murshid here Wednesday night, Iranian Foreign Minister Kamal
Kharrazi underlined the need for continuing the efforts and
initiatives to restore peace and stability in Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
The belligerent sides in the war-ridden country should be
encouraged to hold sincere talks for the sake of understanding and
lasting peace, Kharrazi said.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian foreign minister called for joint measures by the
United Nations, the Organization of the Islamic Conference and
regional states to help solve the Afghan crisis.
</P>
<P>
He welcomed Iran-Pakistan cooperation aimed at improving
medical and living standard of the Afghans.
</P>
<P>
The Pakistani envoy expressed satisfaction with the success of
recent Islamabad-Tehran efforts to send a joint delegation to
Afghanistan for seeking solutions to the crisis.
</P>
<P>
Lauding Iran's pivotal role in peacefully settling the Afghan
crisis, Murshid stressed that the two sides should continue such
efforts before a final settlement is reached.
</P>
<P>
Referring to drug trafficking from Afghanistan, Kharrazi said
that Iran is serious in its campaign against narcotic drugs and
welcomes Pakistan's cooperation in the respect. 
</P>
</TEXT>
