<HEADLINE> Heavy Rain in Sichuan Kills 170 People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Flooding caused by torrential rains
since late June has killed 170 people in southwest China's Sichuan
Province. Total property losses were estimated at 2.5 billion yuan
(about 312.5 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The province was hit by torrential rains beginning on June 27,
as six counties received total rainfall of between 20 to 50
centimeters. More than 1,750 people were injured and another 12
were reported missing in the flood waters following the heavy
downpours.
</P>
<P>
Figures from the Provincial Natural Disaster Relief Office show
that flooding toppled about 60,000 houses and destroyed 58,000
hectares of crops, paralyzing roads and public utilities in many
areas.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government has sent 10 work groups to coordinate
resue operations in the hard-hit areas which, according to local
whether forecasts, are expected to be pelted by heavy rains again
during next few weeks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
