<HEADLINE> HK Industrial Production Falls 4 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's index of industrial
production in the first quarter of 1998 decreased by 4 percent
over the same period of 1997, according to a government survey
released here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The survey, conducted by the Census and Statistics Department,
showed that the output of chemical, rubber, plastic and
non-metallic products fell by 9.5 percent. The output of plastic
products shrank markedly by 18.2 percent due to the weakening in
import demand from the United States and Europe.
</P>
<P>
The output of electrical and electronic products, machinery,
professional equipment and optical goods also declined by 8
percent. Within the group, the output of consumer electrical and
electronic products plunged by 18 percent, partly because of the
relocation of manufacturing processes to the mainland.
</P>
<P>
During the first quarter, the output of paper and printing
products increased slightly by 1.5 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
