<HEADLINE> EU Unemployment Stands at 10.2 Percent in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The seasonally-adjusted
unemployment rate for the 15-nation European Union remained at
10.2 percent in May, Eurostat reported on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
It was the third month running at this level whereas in May
last year the jobless rate was at 10.7 percent and in May 1996 it
was 10.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Luxembourg-based statistical office of the European
communities estimated that 17.1 million men and women were
unemployed within the union in May.
</P>
<P>
Eurostat also reported that the unemployment rate in the euro
zone countries dropped slightly to 11.2 percent in May, compared
with 11.3 percent a month before.
</P>
<P>
The jobless rate for the euro countries was at 11.7 percent in
May last year and 11.6 percent in May 1996.
</P>
<P>
The euro countries include Belgium, Germany, Spain, France,
Ireland, Italy, Luxembourg, the Netherlands, Austria, Portugal and
Finland.
</P>
<P>
Spain's 18.8 percent was still by far the EU's highest
unemployment rate whereas Luxembourg still recorded the union's
lowest jobless record at 2.2 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
