<DOCNO> XIE19980709.0132 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Liaoning Province Developing Deep-Sea Fishing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Liaoning, a coastal province in
northeast China, now leads the country in deep-sea fishing.
</P>
<P>
The province, with 3,000 kilometers of coastline, has 18
ocean-fishing enterprises with 188 fishing vessels. Their
combined catch averages 200,000 tons a year. The figure is
expected to reach 250,000 tons this year, said Chen Xuyi, an
official of the Provincial Marine Department.
</P>
<P>
Four fishing grounds have been opened near West Africa,
South America and in the Pacific Ocean as well as 19 offices all
over the world.
</P>
<P>
Dalian, a leading fishing center in Liaoning, has 100
ocean-going vessels. Dalian has allocated 30 million yuan to set
up an ocean-going fishing fund for sustained development. The city
has so far signed fishing contracts with a dozen countries.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
