<DOCNO> XIE19980709.0133 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Police Spotters Successful in Preventing Violence: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The operation of the police spotters
system has been successful despite the fact that a French gendarme was
beaten into a coma by German hooligans, World Cup organizers said on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Dominique Spinosi, the head for security in the French Organizing
Committee, said on Thursday spotters from German police had identified
450 German hooligans from 30 cities who belonged to the
extremely-right or neo-Nazi groups.
</P>
<P>
She said these hooligans could have gained access to the stadium
and caused more problems if they had not been identified by the
spotters.
</P>
<P>
The system also proved its value after scores of so-called
"Category C" English hooigans were recognized by British police
spotters and sent back home.
</P>
<P>
French gendarme Daniel Nivel remained in coma in hospital but
organizers said he was recovering "slightly day by day." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
