<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> French Newspaper Admits Wrong in Criticising Jacquet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Leading French sports newspaper
L'Equipe admitted that they were wrong in a dispute with French team
manager Aime Jacquet.
</P>
<P>
L'Equipe has fiercely criticised Jacquet's team choices, tactics
and decisions of dropping certain players and cast doubts on Jacquet's
ability of leading the French team in top level tournament like the
World Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
But Jacquet has proved he was right by taking the French team
into the final, the first time ever for France in World Cup history.
</P>
<P>
In a front page editorial, L'Equipe admitted:"The result is that
Jacquet and his men have done what nobody had managed to do before
them, following their own path without flinching."
</P>
<P>
But the newspaper insisted:"We continue not to share his basic
tactical options and to regret deeply certain choices." 
</P>
</TEXT>
