<HEADLINE> Chinese Province Opens State Sector to Foreign Investors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Sichuan Province in southwest China
has listed 122 state-owned enterprises open for foreign
participation, allowing various forms of ownerships, in an effort to
better organize assets.
</P>
<P>
Vice governor Li Dachang announced the arrangement here today
at the '98 Sichuan International Seminar on State-owned
Enterprises Asset Reorganization and Trade Fair.
</P>
<P>
These enterprises were selected from among 15,000 state-owned
businesses in the province in such fields as machinery,
chemicals,light industry, electronics, metallurgy, building
materials, pharmaceuticals, electricity, and nonferrous metals.
</P>
<P>
The possible forms of cooperation include restructuring,
alliance, mergers, purchasing, leasing, stock-controlling, and
contractual management, the official said.
</P>
<P>
Participating overseas partners will be offered favorable
policies. Related departments are providing on-the-spot
services at the fair.
</P>
<P>
Some 120 foreign experts and representatives of overseas
corporations and enterprises are attending the seminar. 
</P>
</TEXT>
