<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Largest Bank Extends More Loans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The ICBC extended a total of 79.7 billion yuan in loans in the
first six months, 23.3 billion yuan more than in the corresponding
period last year, according to bank statistics released today.
</P>
<P>
The newly increased loans raised the bank's value of
outstanding loans to more than 2.07 trillion yuan by the end of
June, including 1.2 trillion yuan in industrial loans and 334.4
billion yuan in commercial loans.
</P>
<P>
The ICBC's outstanding medium- and long-term loans reached
423.3 billion yuan by the end of last month, with lending to the
housing sector rising 1.8 billion yuan in the January-June
period to 45.2 billion yuan by the end of last month.
</P>
<P>
The ICBC has decided to increase loans to railway, highway,
telecommunications and urban construction projects in an effort to
boost national economic growth, a bank official said.
</P>
<P>
Lending will also be increased for the housing sector, the
major state-owned enterprises, small- and medium-sized
enterprises, Sino-overseas joint-ventures, and high-tech projects,
among others, he said.
</P>
<P>
The ICBC has accepted the applications for loans from 52 of the
129 major national highway projects, with potential loans estimated
at 38 billion yuan in all.
</P>
<P>
China has set a target for gross domestic product growth at
eight percent this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
