<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Regulates Accounting Firms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Ministry of Finance
recently announced new procedures governing limited accounting
firms.
</P>
<P>
The detailed regulations include prerequisites for establishing
an accounting firm and specific ratification procedures.
</P>
<P>
Limited liability accounting firms must be sponsored by
certified accountants and operate as social intermediate
organizations engaged in certified accounting. Said firms bear
liabilities equal to their total assets.
</P>
<P>
Establishing a new firm requires at least five qualified
sponsors, a minimum of 10 professional accountants, registered
capital of over 300,000 yuan and offices.
</P>
<P>
Sponsors for firms must be licensed certified accountants with
over three years experience and an unblemished record. Sponsors
are prohibited from holding jobs in other organizations.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
