<DOCNO> XIE19980709.0147 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Stock Market Sees Steady Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 9 (Xinhua) -- China's stock market continued to
grow steadily amid relatively mild fluctuations of key market
indicators in the first half of this year.
</P>
<P>
The number of listed companies on China's two stock exchanges,
in Shanghai and Shenzhen, reached 810 by the end of June, an
increase of 65 from the end of last year, according to official
statistics released today.
</P>
<P>
The total value of shares issued hit a record 210.9 billion
yuan, while the stock market capitalization surged to 2.17
trillion yuan by the end of last month.
</P>
<P>
Generally, the benchmark indicators of the two exchanges showed
an upward trend during the first six months. The Composite Stock
Index tracing performance of stocks in Shanghai opened this year
at 1,194 points and hit a ten-month high of 1,420 before closing
at 1,339 at the end of June. This figure is 12 percent higher than
at the start of this year.
</P>
<P>
The key index for the Shenzhen exchange began this year at 381
points and hit a high of 441 before falling to 403 by the end of
June.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics also show that stock trading in Shanghai
and Shenzhen reached 698.1 billion yuan and 652.7 billion yuan,
respectively, in the January-June period.
</P>
<P>
The listing of four securities investment funds this year,
valued at two billion yuan each, has helped to stabilize the stock
market, experts note.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
