<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed lower Thursday in cautious trading as
the local currency, the ringgit, continued to weaken against the
U.S. dollar.
</P>
<P>
The ringgit slipped to as low as 4.2 per U.S. dollar as against
4.1600/700 at Wednesday's close.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality-stock Composite Index fell 7.39
points to 447.89, the all-share Emas Index slipped 1.62 points to
112.75, the Industrial Index dipped 12.38 points to 917.57 and the
Second Board Index shed 1.22 points to 96.07.
</P>
<P>
Losers led gainers by 382 to 144 while 157 counters were
unchanged and 260 others untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover slipped to 87.676 million shares valued at
167.8 million ringgit (39.857 million U.S. dollars) from 90.112
million shares valued at 195.808 million ringgit (46.51 million
dollars) on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The main board's turnover stood at 83.439 million shares valued
at 162.452 million ringgit (38.587 million dollars) from
Wednesday's 85.924 million shares worth 189.874 million ringgit
(45.1 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the second board was at 4.237 million shares worth
5.348 million ringgit (1.27 million dollars) from 4.188 million
shares valued at 5.934 million ringgit (1.409 million dollars) on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Off-market turnover slipped to 8.439 million shares valued at
40.848 million ringgit (9.702 million dollars) from 45.903 million
shares worth 273.361 million ringgit (64.931 million dollars) on
Wednesday. 
</P>
