<HEADLINE> Nansha Development Zone Blooming in South China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The Nansha economic and
technology development zone has attracted 200 overseas-funded
projects from nearly 20 countries and regions, with total
investments of 1.3 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Located in the city of Fanyu in south China's Guangdong
Province, the development zone was founded on July 8,
1993. During the past five years, the zone has invested three
billion yuan in infrastructural construction.
</P>
<P>
The zone has been appraised as one of the country's top 50
development zones with a favorable investment environment, and was
named a state category-A port in 1997.
</P>
<P>
According to a development zone official, over the next five
years the Nansha zone will expand into more fields welcoming
overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
The Nansha zone has maintained strong momentum in attracting
overseas investment. During the first six months of this year, the
zone signed contracts for 26 projects worth a total of 190 million
U.S. dollars, with 150 million U.S. dollars from overseas
investors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
