<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Australian Bank to Introduce Internet Banking </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Australia's leading bank National
Australia Bank Ltd. (NAB) announced Thursday that it would
introduce an online banking service with unprecedented levels of
security.
</P>
<P>
The service, known as National Internet Banking, would be based
on Java software and feature the use of digital certificates, the
first in the Australian banking market, the bank said.
</P>
<P>
The use of digital certificates is equivalent to an electronic
signature and is assigned to each customer's personal computer.
</P>
<P>
It is encrypted and held on the customer's personal computer,
preventing unauthorized access from any other location.
</P>
<P>
The service would feature online registration, so NAB clients
would not need to visit a branch before using it.
</P>
<P>
It would offer users account balances, 100 days of statement
information with search and sort functions, transfer of funds
between NAB accounts and other banks, secure E-mail to and from
the bank, set up and change periodic payments and bill payments.
</P>
<P>
Glenn Barnes, NAB executive general manager of business and
personal financial services, said national Internet banking would
be made available progressively to NAB staff and selected
customers from this week, with a general release later in the
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980709.0164 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-09 </DATE_TIME>
