Le Figaro:
</P>
<P>
-- Some political activists in the Berber-speaking region of
Kabylie in Algeria said that the appearance of a mysterious Berber
 armed group called ``Armed Berber Movement'' was the outcome of a
 manipulation by some people who want to justify measures of
suppression upon the Berber activists by inciting violence in
Kabylie, a mountainous region east of Algiers which opposes the
law by the government to impose Arabic as the only official
language in Algeria.
</P>
<P>
-- For the first time since the appearance of a great scale
armed struggle in the Yugoslav province of Kosovo, Western powers
showed on Wednesday their growing worry over the rising of
irredentism among the ethnic Albanians of Kosovo. The six-nation
Contact Group on former Yugoslavia Wednesday issued an appeal in
Bonn for an immediate stop to hostility in Kosovo to prepare for
the field of talks between the Yugoslav government and ethnic
Albanians. 
