<HEADLINE> South Africans Drive in to Promote Tourism in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, July 9 (Xinhua) - Ninety motorists in 20 cars
and 18 motorcycles from South Africa have arrived in Dar es
Salaam to promote the country's tourist attraction, media reports
here said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Starting their Africa Friendship Safari late last month, the
motorists have passed through Zimbabwe, Mozambique and Malawi as
well as the regions of Mbeya, Iringa and Morogoro in Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
Leonard Ntimizi, Tanzania's coordinator of the tour, told the
media that they will visit the Dar es Salaam City and the Indian
Ocean beaches before winding up their tour in Zanzibar later this
week and drive back to South Africa.
</P>
<P>
"We expect such a driving mission to create good friendship
among the people and help in promoting Tanzania's tourist sector
within the region," Ntimizi said.
</P>
<P>
The trip was organized by auto mobile associations in South
Africa and was intended to promote tourism in the Southern
African Development Community (SADC) nations.  
