<HEADLINE> Israel Appoints New Chief of General Staff </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, July 9 (Xinhua) -- General Shaul Mofaz was appointed
as the 16th chief of general staff of the Israeli army on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
At a ceremony in the Prime Minister's office here, Mofaz was
also promoted to the rank of Lieutenant General.
</P>
<P>
Mofaz took over the command of the army from Lieutenant
General Amnon Lipkin Shahak, who closed his 36-year service in
the army and finished his three and a half year term of office as
chief of general staff.
</P>
<P>
