<HEADLINE> China Improves Engineering Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 9 (Xinhua) -- China has achieved great success in
improving the quality of various engineering and housing projects
thanks to the highly effective nationwide supervision and
monitoring system.
</P>
<P>
Ye Rutang, vice-minister of construction, said today that a
large number of key projects and numerous urban infrastructure
projects, as well as nearly one billion sq.m., have either reached
advance international standards or government quality standards.
</P>
<P>
In addition, breakthroughs have been made in the planning,
design and construction of the country's engineering and housing
projects, and substantial progress has been made in environmental
protection and more infrastructure facilities have been completed.
</P>
<P>
One senior official pointed out that more than 90 percent of
China's cities and counties have set up engineering quality
supervision stations, with related departments covering over 88
percent of the nation's construction projects.
</P>
<P>
China has also established engineering monitoring institutes
which handled or prevented over 60,000 construction hazards
in recent years.
</P>
<P>
However, many problems remain in spite of the progress, with
particular problems centered on residential housing, according to
Ye. The vice-minister reiterated that a great deal of work must
still be carried out in related activities.  
</P>
