<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Henan Reaps Good Summer Grain Harvest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Despite suffering from several
natural disasters, the major grain-producing province of Henan has
just reaped a summer grain harvest of 20.951 billion kilograms.
</P>
<P>
This output is the second highest ever for the inland province
of central China, only 12.7 percent less than last summer's
record harvest.
</P>
<P>
Though the hectarage of grain-producing land has been
increased, the province has been suffering from droughts, low
temperature, plant diseases and insect infestation since last
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
