<HEADLINE> Malaysia's Sabah Selected to Locate Broadcast Station </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Sabah, East Malaysia, has been
selected as the location for the world time broadcast station to
serve as a reference center for countries in the region and
Australia, Sabah State Deputy Chief Minister Joseph Kurup said
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
This station will serve as a time reference center for ASEAN
countries and the southern part of China as well as the western
and northern parts of Australia, Kurup said when opening a seminar
in the state's capital of Kota Kinabalu, Malaysia's news agency
Bernama reported.
</P>
<P>
The station, to be located at Keningau as offered by the state
government, could provide automatic time synchronization for
computers and wrist watches equipped with decoder chips within a
25,000-kilometer radius.
</P>
<P>
The station project is expected to get off the ground next
year.
</P>
<P>
There are already three world time stations existing in the
United Kingdom, Germany and China respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
