<HEADLINE> Thuram Insists He Is No Hero </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Lilian Thuram, who scored the two
goals to put France into World Cup final against Brazil, insisted
that he was no hero.
</P>
<P>
"I'm no hero. I did my best as usual but the team won, not just
me." said the surprise scorer in the semi-final match.
</P>
<P>
Thuram had never scored a single goal in his 37 previous
appearances for France. But he scored twice to give France its
first World Cup final.
</P>
<P>
"If you say it's a nice goal, then it must be," Thuram said,
"But what counts is that we're in the final, all 22 of us. We
worked very hard for it and we deserve it."
</P>
<P>
French coach Aime Jacquet said:"The two goals scored by Lilian
are a great reward for us but especially for him. He deserves it.
He has had such a great World Cup." 
</P>
