<HEADLINE> Ugandan Mayor to Be Questioned on Return: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Mayor of Uganda's capital city
Kampala Hajji Nasser Sebaggala will be questioned by Interpol
even if he wins the case in the United States and returns home, a
minister said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Tom Butime, the minister of internal affairs, was quoted by
Thursday's New Vision as making the remarks in the parliament.
</P>
<P>
"When Sebaggala comes back he will tell us how, where and with
whom he has been dealing in Bicupuli (fake checks). Interpol will
be interested," the minister said.
</P>
<P>
