House roaring with laughter.
</P>
<P>
Sebaggala, arrested on June 13, has been detained in the
United States pending his trial on alleged financial fraud
charges and making false statements to the U.S. customs officers
there.
</P>
<P>
Some members of parliament blamed the Ugandan government for
refusing to help the democratically elected mayor who is now in
trouble.
</P>
<P>
Butime said: "Government has provided normal consular services
like it does with other national...Now this is a matter for
Sebaggala to handle within the U.S. legal system."
</P>
<P>
When in New York, the embattled mayor was fed and housed by
Uganda's Ambassador to the United States free of charge, he
added. 
