<HEADLINE> Shanghai Students Attend Summer Camps </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 9 (Xinhua) -- A large number of students in
Shanghai, China's leading economic and financial center, are
attending summer camps designed to promote endurance.
</P>
<P>
The Island Summer Endurance Camp, organized by Shanghai
Municipal Committee of the Communist Youth League of China (CYLC),
attracted more than 100 students on the first half day of
registration. with the number of applicants far exceeding the
expected figure.
</P>
<P>
Experts stress that nurturing a child in favorable conditions
which enable them to experience hardships promotes their sense of
independence and fosters their spirit of mutual assistance under
difficult conditions.
</P>
<P>
The summer camp's program agenda includes cleaning facilities,
camping, field exercises, reclaiming and cultivating Changdao
Island of east China's Shandong Province.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Youth Travel Service, and organization which
caters to the needs of the market, joined the Shanghai Municipal
Committee of the CYLC in sponsoring summer camps in Beijing and
Jinggang Mountains, a strategic revolutionary base in east China's
Jiangxi Province.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the camps attract substantially more boys
willing to endure hardships.
</P>
<P>
Experts pointed out that arranging summer camps still falls far
short of the needs in a city with hundreds of thousands of
youngsters.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, the travel agencies are currently arranging weekend
outings to Chongming Farm where many of the participant's parents
once worked.  
</P>
</TEXT>
