<HEADLINE> China, U.S. to Promote Original Software </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 9 (Xinhua) -- China Software Alliance (CSA) and
the U.S.-based Business Software Alliance (BSA) will continue
their cooperation promoting the use of original software in China.
</P>
<P>
The two organizations will jointly launch the second phase of
the Original Software Users Recognition Program, which is a
follow-up of the program officially initiated in May last year.
</P>
<P>
The program is aimed at encouraging the usage of original
software and enhancing intellectual property rights (IPR)
protection.
</P>
<P>
During the second phase, those companies or organizations that
participate in the program and are committed to using original
software and implementing internal software management will
receive a preferential package from a CSA or a BSA member company.
</P>
<P>
Through various channels, CSA and BSA will publicize the
participating companies and organizations.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the start of this program in China, BSA also worked in
cooperation with relevant Chinese governmental departments by
holding a workshop on IPR enforcement techniques in Beijing and by
launching a hotline for reporting the illegal use of software.
</P>
