<HEADLINE> Croatia Defender Says Blanc Gets What He Deserves </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Croatia defender Slaven Bilic said
that Laurent Blanc of France got what he deserved by missing the
World Cup final match.
</P>
<P>
Blanc pushed Bilic on the face in the semi-final match between
France and Croatia and that earned him a red card and automatically
missed the final.
</P>
<P>
"I didn't get him sent off. He touched me. Technically that's
an offence and the referee saw it," said Bilic, "I'm not happy that
he's going to miss the final but if you do something like that
you're going to get punished."
</P>
<P>
Blanc said:"I admit I made a mistake and lost control but even
when the referee came towards me I thought it would only be a yellow
card, not a red."
</P>
<P>
"For me it is a personal catastrophe, but it wasn't for the
team, because they won. My thoughts are for them now." said Blanc.
</P>
