<HEADLINE> French Press Cool after France Enters Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The French press was cool on Thursday
in reacting to the entry for the first time by France into the
final of the World Cup by beating Croatia 2-1 Wednesday evening.
</P>
<P>
The daily Liberation said that Sunday, the day when France
faces Brazil, will not be like Wednesday, because Brazil is not
Croatia.
</P>
<P>
"Ronaldo, Rivaldo, Bebeto and company play great football.
Attack, defense and pleasure. The champions of the world in title
are the last obstacle to the French Valhalla," said the newspaper.
</P>
<P>
The daily Parisien-Aujourd'hui paid hommage to the defenser of
the French team Thuram who scored twice on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"Last night, he is great. His double pushed France to the final
of the World Cup, for the first time of her history. She will be
the 11th country to know this honor since the creation of the
competition in 1930," it said.
</P>
<P>
The France Soir said half jokingly that the "anti-football
martyrs" only have four days to suffer before the frenzy of the
World Cup ends.
</P>
<P>
"You will have no more cries, enthusiasm, and the happy crowd
on the Champs-Elysee from the whole world," it said.
</P>
<P>
The Marseille-based daily Provence said that football has gone
beyond sports and has become a phenomenon of society.
</P>
<P>
"We think about the children of Castellane, the popular city in
the northern part of Marseille, where a certain Zinedine Zidane
grew up. Today, the children of the district all have their eyes
on him," said the daily in reference to an immigrants' district of
the Mediterranean metropolis.
</P>
<P>
The Berry Republicain said that the World Cup shows that sports
can be the "ferment of solidarity" of all societies, because when
people watch the game, they forget things like unemployment and
social exclusion.
</P>
<P>
The daily Nouvelle Republique du Centre-Ouest said that the
game with Croatia was a trap, because it was unfair for the French
to show such great fighting emotion toward Croatia which has never
done any harm to France in history. 
</P>
