<HEADLINE> Joint Enterprise Training Centers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Zhejiang University and the Hong
Kong Politechnic University have jointly opened an international
enterprise training center in Hangzhou, capital of Zhejiang
Province.
</P>
<P>
The center will foster highly competent administrators capable
of managing enterprises in both inland areas and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Zhejiang University is one of China's biggest universities and
Hong Kong Politechnic maintains extensive industrial and
commercial ties.
</P>
<P>
The center will offer high quality MBA and enterprise
administration courses.
</P>
<P>
Courses will focus on industry, commerce, financial affairs,
marketing and quality control.
</P>
<P>
The center will enable university graduates to earn a master's
degree from Hong Kong Politechnic.
</P>
<P>
The training center plans to offer courses taught by visiting
scholars and experts from throughout the world.  
