<HEADLINE> Modern Enterprise System Shows Good Results in Liaoning </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The pilot establishment of the
modern enterprise system in northeast China's Liaoning Province,
an old heavy industrial base built under a planned economy, is now
showing initial good results.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, 79 percent of the the province's
126 enterprises chosen for the experiment, which began three years
ago, have been making profits.
</P>
<P>
The 126 enterprises have all completed the work of
rectification, verifying assets and demarcating property rights,
and have scientific management systems in place.
</P>
<P>
Eighty-nine of these enterprises have finished system
reshuffling in accordance with Corporate Law, while 60 percent
have set up shareholders congresses, and boards of directors and
supervisory councils.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, the total assets of the 126 enterprises was 200
billion yuan, a rise of 13 percent over 1996, according to the
sources. 
</P>
</TEXT>
