<HEADLINE> Hungary's New Cabinet Sworn in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, July 8 (Xinhua) -- In just two days after the
swearing in oath taken by Prime Minister Orban Viktor, the
18-member new cabinet was sworn in Wednesday afternoon at the
parliamentary building.
</P>
<P>
President Goencz Arpad issued the letter of appointment for all
the cabinet members and presided over the inaugural ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The new cabinet was the third government and the youngest one
since 1990. The average age of the members is only 49.6 years old.
</P>
<P>
The Fidesz-MPP party, headed by Orban, won 148 seats in the
386-seat National Assembly during legislative elections in May.
</P>
<P>
It has forged a coalition with the rural-based Independent
Smallholder's Party, with 48 seats, and the conservative Hungarian
Democratic Forum with 17 seats.
</P>
<P>
Born in Szekesfehervar, a city 50 kilometers southwest of
Budapest, Orban became a founding member of the Fidesz-MPP in
1988, at the age of 25.
</P>
<P>
He was elected into the National Assembly in 1990, rose to the
chair of the Fidesz-MPP in 1993 and became a parliamentary member
again in 1994, heading the commission for European integration
affairs. 
</P>
