<HEADLINE> Five Ethnic Albanians Killed in Conflict in Border Village </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRISTINA, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Five ethnic Albanians were killed
and several other wounded Wednesday as a result of a heaviest
attack launched by Serb police against a long-besieged separatist
enclave on the Albanian border, the Associated Press quoted ethnic
Albanian sources as saying.
</P>
<P>
The ethnic Albanian Kosovo Information Center was quoted as
saying the escalation of fighting around the mountainous border
village of Morina was accompanied by Serb shelling of at least
four other area villages.
</P>
<P>
The assault appears to be an attempt to cut off Kosovo Albanian
militants from Albania, which believed to be the main source of
weapons for ethnic Albanian separatists in the breakaway
province. The report has not been confirmed by the Yugoslav
government.
</P>
<P>
More than 300 people have been killed in Kosovo since ethnic
Albanian separatists intensified their separatist campaign in
February. Kosovo is a province in northern Serbia with 90 percent
of its 1.8 million population ethnic Albanians.
</P>
<P>
The fighting came amid international efforts to resume talks
between the Yugoslav federal government and ethnic Albanian
separatists.
</P>
<P>
The North Atlantic Treaty Organisation has threatened to use
military action to restore peace in the troubled area if peace
talks fail. 
</P>
