<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Asean Tiger Cup Football to be Held in Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, July 8 (Xinhua) -- The second Asean Tiger Cup football
tuornament will be hosted by Vietnam's Hanoi and Ho Chi Minh city,
Vietnam News Agency (VNA) reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Asean Football Federation (AFF) officially informed the
Vietnam Football Federation (VFF) on Tuesday that Hanoi and Ho Chi
Minh city have been chosen as host cities of the second Tiger Cup
to be held from August 26 to September 5.
</P>
<P>
Eight teams from Malaysia, Singapore, Laos, Indonesia, the
Philippines, Thailand, Myanmar, and Vietnam, divided into two
groups, will play 16 matches at the Hanoi Stadium and Ho Chi Minh
city's Thong Nhat (unification) Stadiums.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia and Singapore will play the opening match of group B
which also includes Laos and Vietnam in Hanoi, while Indonesia and
the Philippines will play the opening match of group A in Ho Chi
Minh city.
</P>
<P>
The bi-annual Tiger Cup is Southeast Asia's biggest football
tournament and the largest tournament of its kind ever hosted by
Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
Necessary preparations for the event have been carried out by
the Vietnam's Sports and Physical Training Committee and relevant
agencies.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam's national football team has been convened for their
second training session in Vietnam's central highlands city of Da
Lat.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam was asked by the Asean Football Federation (AFF) to
step in as a last-minute replacement for Malaysia, which had
originally been chosen to host the cup as a second choice to
Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia had its offer withdrawn because of on-going economic
difficulties. Malaysia's decision to host the Commonwealth Games
this September was cited by the AFF as the reason for the shifting
the event to another country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
