<HEADLINE> Shanghai Sells Life Insurance Policy for Mortgage Borrowers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai, China's largest
metropolis, has begun selling a special life insurance policy for
home buyers who take out mortgage loans.
</P>
<P>
The policy, available to people between 18 and 55 years old, is
designed to prevent insolvency due to the death or injury of the
borrower.
</P>
<P>
The policy is for the same term as the mortgage, according to
the Shanghai branch of the Life Insurance Company under the
People's Insurance Company of China (PICC) Group.
</P>
<P>
This policy has been welcomed by both borrowers and local
banks, as the first half of this year saw a rapid growth in the
number of mortgage borrowers in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai branch of the China Construction Bank, which
accounts for 90 percent of the local mortgage market, recorded
3.42 billion yuan (about 412 million US dollars) in mortgage loans
for housing in the first half of the year, an increase of more
than 30 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
