<HEADLINE> Germany Calls up Becker for Davis Cup Quarter-final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Germany have called up semi-retired
Boris Becker for the Davis Cup world group quarter-final against
defending champions Sweden in Hamburg, Germany on July 17-19.
</P>
<P>
The German team Captain Carl-Uwe Steeb has lined up the
30-year-old Becker alongside Nicolas Kiefer, Tommy Haas and David
Prinosil.
</P>
<P>
Sweden's captain Carl-Axel Hageskog will rely on Jonas
Bjorkman, Thomas Enqvist, Magnus Larsson and Nicklas Kulti, the
same team that won the trophy after beating the United States in
the final in Gothenburg last year.
</P>
<P>
The Swedish team will arrive in Hamburg later. 
</P>
</TEXT>
