<HEADLINE> Additional Chinese Aid Arrives in DPRK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PYONGYANG, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The 100,000 tons of food and
20,000 tons of fertilizer donated by China in additional aid to
the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) had arrived by
July 6, the official DPRK news media reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The donations were promised by the Chinese government on April
13.
</P>
<P>
The aid will encourage the Korean people to fight natural
disasters and achieve a final success, the official media said.
</P>
<P>
The assistance is in addition to 150,000 tons of food relief
aid China offered the DPRK last year in a bid to ease food
shortages resulting from two consecutive years of natural
disasters. 
