<HEADLINE> Four Seeds Upset in Hall of Fame Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Four seeded players were upset
at the second round matchess of the Hall of Fame Tennis
Championships in Newport, Rhode Island on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Second seed Mark Woodforde of Australia lost to Italy's
Laurence Tieleman 4-6, 6-3, 6-2 and third-seeded American Jeff
Tarango was knocked out by his compatriot Justin Gimelstob 3-6,
6-1, 7-6 (7-4).
</P>
<P>
Indian Leander Paes downed sixth seed Scott Draper of Australia
7-5, 6-4 while Bahamian qualifier Mark Knowles ousted
eighth-seeded South African Grant Stafford, the 1996 runner-up in
Newport, 7-5, 4-6, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Top seed Australian Jason Stoltenberg's second round encounter
with countryman Lleyton Hewitt was postponed. 
