<HEADLINE> Central China's Province Ready to Fight Flood </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Central China's Hubei Province has
spent 1.35 billion yuan since last winter to strengthen 210,000
water conservancy projects and reinforce 79.9 million cubic meters
of dikes.
</P>
<P>
The Yangtze River flood season came earlier than usual
this year, bringing heavy rains to the middle and lower
reaches of the river.
</P>
<P>
China's meteorological departments have predicted that between
June and August, the middle and lower reaches of the Yangtze
River will get even more rain, and that some areas, including
Hubei Province, will be hit by serious flooding.
</P>
<P>
Hubei Province has prepared communications equipment, prepared
1.7 million cubic meters of sands and stone barriers for flood
fighting, and 1.2 million people are ready for the campaign
against the anticipated floods.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
