<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Forbidden City Opera to Resound Worldwide </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The sounds of Puccini's opera
"Turandot", recounting the spell-binding story of a Chinese
princess, will resound in her legendary home of Beijing's
Forbidden City in September.
</P>
<P>
Famous Chinese film director Zhang Yimou and one of the world's
leading opera conductors Zubin Mehta will join forces to create
one of the century's last major operatic events, according to
today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
The combination of these two talents will attract 15,000 to
20,000 opera fans from all over the world to the Imperial
Ancestral Temple, according to Michael Ecker, the opera's
executive producer, at a press conference yesterday.
</P>
<P>
Ecker is representing Opera On Original Site Inc From
Switzerland, which has worked closely with the China Performing
Arts Agency to make the project come to fruition.
</P>
<P>
An estimated 1 billion viewers worldwide will watch the show
live on television, he said.
</P>
<P>
The performance will also help realize the long-cherished dream
of many artists and opera fans to see Turandot in her own home.
</P>
<P>
"Turandot", one of the most popular and frequently performed of
Puccini's operas, was developed from what Westerners believe to
be a Chinese fairy tale. It tells how a Persian prince thaws the
revenge and hatred of Chinese princess Turandot, and wins her heart
with his love in the Forbidden City.
</P>
<P>
"I am extremely excited that my dream performance of "Turandot'
in its original setting is coming true," said Zubin Mehta in
Munich via videophone.
</P>
<P>
"I believe that the staging of "Turandot' in Beijing will
further demonstrate that the arts, whether opera or film, are the
best media for people of different cultures and histories to
communicate with each other and to share their feelings and
emotions," said Zhang Yimou, the director of the production.
</P>
<P>
Total investment in the project is estimated at 15 million US
dollars (or 124.5 million Renminbi yuan).  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980709.0296 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Results of Austrian Women's Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
