<HEADLINE> U.N. Panel to Visit Algeria on July 22 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, July 8 (Xinhua) -- A penal of eminent persons
set up by U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan on fact-finding
mission to Algeria is scheduled to start its work on July 22, it
was announced here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Chairman of the panel, former Portuguese President Mario
Soares, said the discussions between panel members and Annan on
Wednesday have resulted in a decision for the panel to leave
Lisbon for Algeria on July 22.
</P>
<P>
Soares' team includes I.K. Gujiral, former Indian Prime
Minister, Abdel Karim Kabariti, former Jordan Prime Minister,
Donald McHenry, former U.S. Permanent Representative to the U.N.,
Simone Veil, former French Secretary of State and Amos Wako,
Attorney General of Kenya.
</P>
<P>
They are expected to stay in Algeria for about two weeks, to be
followed by their report to Annan. The report will be made public,
a U.N. spokesman said in a brief statement Wednesday.  
</P>
</TEXT>
