<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Moldovan Economic Entities Appealed to Pay Taxes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Parliament Chairman of Moldova
Dumitru Diacov Wednesday called on enterprise heads and
businessmen of the Republic to pay timely taxes.
</P>
<P>
The Chairman stated that the Moldovan economy is on the verge
of a crash, and the population leads a miserable life. Under these
conditions the government and the Parliament are going to take
certain extraordinary measures to bring the financial sphere in
order.
</P>
<P>
Certain taxes will be tightened and their base will be
expanded, extra sanctions will be introduced against tax evasion,
he stressed, adding that it is planned to abolish a number of
privileges granted to some economic entities.
</P>
<P>
Dumitru Diacov said that the strategy of the new government and
Parliament is not only to prevent a social unrest, but also to
save the country from the crisis, to restore its economic
development, to fight corruption in all the spheres.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that tax evasion must be stopped once and for ever.
The businessmen must pay taxes on time and regularly.
</P>
<P>
The total debt of economic entities on value added taxes and
excises stands at 73.76 million lei (about 15.7 million U.S.
dollars), a recent official release showed.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
