<HEADLINE> Croatia Coach Not Disappointed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
SAINT-DENIS, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Croatia coach Miroslav Blazevic
said he had nothing to be ashamed of after suffering a 2-1 loss to
the host team France on Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
"They reacted very well after we scored our goal. When they
levelled, they found strength and our team did not have any more.
France are a very compact team and I wish them luck." Blazevic said.
</P>
<P>
Striker Goran Vlaovic said:"We're very proud. I think we had a
very good game. It was a really tough, hard game against a very
good team."
</P>
<P>
"I wouldn't say France's equalizer was a decisive moment but it
was just one of those things." said Vlaovic. 
</P>
