<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Crime Level Down in Maldova </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Moldova registered 18,816 crimes
and offenses in the first half of 1998, a 1.4-percent decrease as
compared with the same period of 1997, the Moldovan BASA-Press
news agency reported on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The number of serious crimes dropped 4.8 percent, injuries
dropped 16.4 percent and thefts from foreign firms dropped 48
percent. Economic offenses dropped 14.4 percent. At the same time
the number of pickpockets increased 43.9 percent, hooliganism 10.5
percent.
</P>
<P>
The decrease of the crime rate is due to the efficiency of the
police's special operations on crime prevention, according to
Interior experts.  
</P>
</TEXT>
