<HEADLINE> Dow Approaching Record Level </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Stocks on Wall Street rose toward
record levels today with the Dow Jones industrial average jumping
89.93 points to 9,174.97.
</P>
<P>
The Dow's gain in 1998 has been extended to 16 percent and is
now about 77 points from May 13's record of 9,211.84.
</P>
<P>
The blue-chip advance also pushed higher broader stock indexes.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 rose 11.71 to a record 1,166.37,
pushing this year's gain above 20 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Nasdaq composite index rose 27.28 to a record 1,935.39, up
23.2 percent for the year.
</P>
<P>
Advancers outnumbered decliners by a 7-to-5 margin on the New
York Stock Exchange, with 1,751 up, 1,241 down and 547 unchanged.
The ratio of winners to losers was even smaller in Nasdaq trading.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE composite index rose 4.59 to a record 594.35. NYSE
volume totaled 605.36 million shares, down from 628.33 million on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Russell 2000 index of smaller companies rose 0.61 to 459.66,
and the American Stock Exchange composite index rose 0.69 to
728.65.
</P>
<P>
Travelers jumped more than 4 U.S. dollars to 68.81 dollars to
lead the Dow after a Merrill Lynch analyst issued an upbeat
assessment of Citigroup, the new company to be formed by the
impending merger with Citicorp, which surged 9 dollars to 170.25
dollars today.
</P>
</TEXT>
