<HEADLINE> Jacquet Satisfied with Team's Performance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
SAINT-DENIS, July 8 (Xinhua) -- French team manager Aime Jacquet
said he was very satisfied with his team's performance in the match
against Croatia.
</P>
<P>
The host team won the semi-final match 2-1 thanks to two goals
from defender Lilian Thuram.
</P>
<P>
"It was a very tough game. Croatia is a very good team and they
played very well." said Jacquet.
</P>
<P>
"But we played even better. Our players were very tired as they
have played 5 games, including two extra-time." Jacquet said.
</P>
<P>
"Thuram saved us by scoring the two goals. Now we are in the
final against Brazil," said Jacquet, "Brazil are the best team in
the world but anyway, we have to play against them."
</P>
<P>
French team captain Didier Deschamps admitted he was very tired
in the match:"We were exhausted, but we prevailed and won the match."
</P>
<P>
"The Croatia team are one of the best teams in the world, they are
very well technically and the match against them were very tough."
said Deschamps.
</P>
<P>
"We lacked concentration when we conceded the goal at the
beginning of the second half," said Deschamps, "But we soon calmed
down and Thuram hit in the equaliser in time to boost our morale."
</P>
<P>
"Marcel Desailly is our best defender and in the match against
Brazil, I think it will be his job to mark Ronaldo." Deschamps said.
</P>
</TEXT>
